Cell[CellGroupData[{

Cell["AxesToEuler", "Section",
 PageWidth->WindowWidth,
 Evaluatable->False,
 InitializationCell->True,
 InitializationGroup->True,
 AspectRatioFixed->
  False,ExpressionUUID->"7bf8439f-f070-4093-9813-6c82af603e59"],

Cell["\<\
AxesToEuler::usage = 
\t\"AxesToEuler[system2,system1,opts] gives the Euler angles \
\[CapitalOmega]21={\[Alpha]21,\[Beta]21,\[Gamma]21} by which each axis of \
system2 may be rotated around the system1 axes in order to be brought into \
coincide with the corresponding axis of system1:
\t\te\[Micro]1=Rz1(\[Alpha]21)Ry1(\[Beta]21)Rz1(\[Gamma]21).e\[Micro]2, where \
\[Mu]\[Element]{x,y,z}.
The same result is generated by rotating around the system2 axes:
\t\te\[Micro]1=Rz2(\[Alpha]21)Ry2(\[Beta]21)Rz2(\[Gamma]21).e\[Micro]2, where \
\[Mu]\[Element]{x,y,z}.
The same result is also generated by using \\\"moving axes\\\", where the \
axes follow the Euler rotations, but in this case the angles are applied in \
reverse order:
\t\te\[Micro]1=Rz2'(\[Gamma]21)Ry2'(\[Beta]21)Rz2(\[Alpha]21).e\[Micro]2, 
where the primed axes of system1 follow the rotation.  

In a typical application, system2 is the principal axis system P of an \
anisotropic interaction, and system1 is a reference axis system such as a \
molecular frame M, or the laboratory frame L. The routine AxesToEuler[P,M] \
then generates the Euler angles \[CapitalOmega]PM which would be used in \
spherical tensor realisations of the spin Hamiltonian. 

Each of system1 and system2 may have the form {Z} or {X,Z} or {X,Y,Z}. Here \
Z,X and Y are 3-vectors. If only Z is specified, the two remaining axes are \
constructed. If X and Z is specified, the z-axis of the constructed system is \
equal to Z and the x-axis is in the XZ plane. If all three axes are \
specified, they must be a right-handed orthogonal set.
If system1 is missing, the system {ex,ey,ez} is assumed.

AxesToEuler also accepts axis definitions containing symbolic angles; in this \
case the symbolic result assumes that all angles are in the first quadrant \
(i.e. greater than 0 and less than \[Pi]/2).
\";\
\>", "Input",
 PageWidth->WindowWidth,
 InitializationCell->True,
 InitializationGroup->True,
 CellChangeTimes->{{3.409668303694035*^9, 3.409668508820278*^9}, {
   3.409812645318563*^9, 3.409812995932979*^9}, 3.409813082155493*^9, {
   3.502955889240649*^9, 3.50295590149749*^9}, {3.673944867633757*^9, 
   3.673944901802813*^9}, {3.6739483993910933`*^9, 3.673948403866509*^9}, {
