   3.673963427090214*^9, 3.673963457395441*^9}, {3.6739634875591297`*^9, 
   3.673963509146616*^9}, {3.6739635499866543`*^9, 3.673963551615808*^9}, {
   3.690699740606904*^9, 3.690699814012726*^9}, {3.69069995095348*^9, 
   3.690700076211907*^9}},
 AspectRatioFixed->
  True,ExpressionUUID->"353cb85f-7a61-4386-9d74-8c1cec77ab12"]
}, Closed]],

Cell[CellGroupData[{

Cell["RotateEuler", "Section",
 PageWidth->WindowWidth,
 Evaluatable->False,
 InitializationCell->True,
 InitializationGroup->True,
 AspectRatioFixed->
  True,ExpressionUUID->"e68bced3-bad7-43ef-964c-02dd855722e4"],

Cell["\<\
RotateEuler::usage =
\t\"RotateEuler[obj,{\[Alpha],\[Beta],\[Gamma]},axes] rotates the vector \
according to the Euler angles {\[Alpha],\[Beta],\[Gamma]} around the \
specified axes.

axes may have the form {z}, {x,z} or {x,y,z} (see routine AxisSystem).

If axes are missing, the system {ex,ey,ez} is assumed.
\t\t
For example, RotateEuler[obj,{\[Alpha],\[Beta],\[Gamma]},{vx,vy,vz}] rotates \
obj by the angle \[Gamma] about the axis vz, followed by a rotation by the \
angle \[Beta] about vy, followed by a rotation through the angle \[Alpha] \
about vz.

The same rotations may be performed in the order \
\[Alpha]\[Rule]\[Beta]\[Rule]\[Gamma] about the axes vz\[Rule]vy'\[Rule]vz'' \
where the axes {vx,vy',vz''} are simultaneously rotated together with the \
object.

If the Euler angles relating two axis systems sys1 and sys2 are deduced using \
{\[Alpha]12,\[Beta]12,\[Gamma]12}=AxesToEuler[sys1,sys2], then the axis \
system sys1 may be superimposed on the axis system sys2 using the rotation \
RotateEuler[sys1,{\[Alpha]12,\[Beta]12,\[Gamma]12},sys1].

The object obj may be a 3-vector, an axis system, or contain lines, polygons, \
and text.
\";\
\>", "Input",
 PageWidth->WindowWidth,
 InitializationCell->True,
 InitializationGroup->True,
 CellChangeTimes->{{3.409668587378058*^9, 3.409668701859187*^9}, {
  3.409823473540504*^9, 3.409823474061829*^9}, {3.6739387789763308`*^9, 
  3.6739389100449743`*^9}},
 AspectRatioFixed->
  True,ExpressionUUID->"bae752b9-6a58-4ff8-b805-4e53c5e99bb7"]
}, Closed]],

